args:
When the prince and his allies eke out a win
against the androids, Ex Machina orders Finni to
self-destruct in an attempt to kill Laxi. But when
the others save Finni, Eirene leaves Ex Machina
and aligns herself with the prince.
Main forces have suffered catastrophic\nlosses! We can't take any more!
The writing is on the wall, Eirene.\nFurther battle serves no purpose.
Perhaps not when it comes to achieving\nEx Machina's objective...
But for me, there IS a purpose\nif it means I can destroy you!
▷Laxi, watch out!◁\nShe has launched a direct attack and\nover-committed. It is not a threat.
(If I were to take an attack from that\nmobile weapon in this state...)
Ungh... Eirene... I'll protect you...\nI'LL PROTECT YOOOOU!
Oh no... She's losing control!\nFinni, stop! Stand down!
I'm afraid of losing control of myself,\nand also of breaking down.
But the thing I'm the most\nafraid of is losing you!
So if I'm going to break down, I want it to\nbe for your sake! I'll be the one to destroy\nyour enemies!
▷Wait, she CHOSE to lose control?!◁\nMascula, focus! She's coming!
No, Finni. It's wrong. This is all wrong.\nI'm the one who can't lose YOU!
Which is why I'm shutting you down!
Huh? The shutdown command didn't work!
Unit Finni has lost control.\nSwitching to self-destruct mode.
Anassa has revoked my authority and\nengaged her self-destruct remotely...
Is this your answer, Anassa?\nIs this the judgment of Ex Machina?!
We need to get out of here\nbefore she destructs!
▷If she blows up, there's no telling how\nmuch damage she could do to Luca and\nall of the others!◁
The only options would be to disable the\nself-destruct system or completely destroy\nthe unit, and there isn't time for either.

If we knew the location of the self-destruct
device, there's one other way, but there's
not enough time to find it.
▷In that case...◁
▷Eirene, tell us where Finni's self-\ndestruct is located so we can save her!◁
You are the enemy!\nWhy would I help you?!
▷Because if you don't, Finni dies.\nIs that a price you're willing to pay?◁
...We are Ex Machina.\nWe're nothing more than tools who\nobey orders. So obey I must.
▷You're lying to yourself!\nSure, we're androids. We were built as\ntools. But remember what you told me!◁
▷You said that even androids have things\nthat are important to them. Remember?!◁
▷I want to help everyone—\nincluding Finni and you!◁
Her neck! It's at the base of her neck!
I absorbed the mana around the device\nas I removed it. Without mana,\nit no longer functions.
Due to your actions, unit Eirene,\ndestruction of the enemy unit has failed.
Your actions benefited our enemy;\nsuch conduct does not befit Ex Machina.
Yes, that's right: I do not befit Ex Machina.
The Ark and Ex Machina mean nothing\nto me when compared to the life of Finni.
And since you tried to hurt her,\nI can no longer obey you.
The Ark will be informed that units\nEirene and Finni are a detriment to\nEx Machina.
Doubtless the Humanoid Liberation Agency\nwill take appropriate measures.
They can do as they wish. For my part,\nI shall live with Finni to the very end.
There is no meaning in the existence of\nan android removed from Ex Machina.
I decide the meaning of my own existence;\nthat is why I have a heart, after all.\nIs it not the same for you, Anassa?
Yet another meaningless question.\nMy heart says but one thing:
For the future of all humanoid life,\nand Ex Machina.
Well, my former commander. It seems I\nhave been expelled from Ex Machina.
Find a place to hide, first and foremost.\nEx Machina will not be content to leave\nus to our own devices.
Then why not come to the Halidom?
Eh, what's one more weirdo in that place?\nWhatcha think, {player_name}?
Well, there's a lot we'll need to learn\nabout them, but I have a feeling they're\ngoing to make fine allies.
Are you serious? You know we were trying\nto end your lives not an hour ago, yes?
But you are no longer doing so.\n▷Ha ha ha! Well, at the very least,\nwe don't have a reason to fight anymore.◁
In that case, we accept your offer.\nThank you for having us.
Well, this isn't nearly as broken\nas I thought it would be.
It would be a terrible waste to just\nleave this toy lying here...
Given the opportunity, I think I shall\nsee what use I can make of it...
